Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.92,0:00:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, who came to Munich, found herself in her \Nformer place, after switching places with Luise once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.66,0:00:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, what you can't call anything else \Nbut a quirk of fate, came into play -
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.86,0:00:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow, the entire family of four \Nhappened to have come together for Palfy's concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.24,0:00:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But what will become of it now?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.43,0:00:27.34,Sign,,0,0,125,,{\c&HEAFCF9&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 17 \N {\fs35} Munich in an Uproar! \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.74,0:00:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Section A, seat three.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.09,0:00:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.57,0:00:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte..!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.72,0:00:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.57,0:01:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Seats one and two of the A section...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.12,0:01:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's more to the front, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.96,0:01:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.39,0:01:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! Annie and her dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.37,0:01:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Annie, it's here, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.77,0:01:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, let's sit...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.93,0:01:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie, that dress looks perfect on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.73,0:01:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's eyes are on you tonight! {/you're like an angel}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.23,0:01:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But hey, father, those concerts are the most boring stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.44,0:01:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie, you should know, \Nthere are not many people in Munich as rich as we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.75,0:01:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Our duty is to spend money on refined pastimes, \Na "richnesse oblige," so to say! {lit is "rich have no choice but to have such elegant; graceful; refined hobbies/tastes" but he laughs afterwards so I added a joke}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.69,0:01:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on, Luise? {/do we do}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.39,0:01:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We're between the hammer and the anvil! {certain end of life; death; breathing one's last}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.45,0:01:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And nowhere else to run! {/now it's all over}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.22,0:01:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? What is it, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.43,0:01:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.78,0:01:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.20,0:02:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.43,0:02:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Munich's first intrepid lady. \NSomething like Frau Körner, isn't it? {he just says "munich one strong-willed; strong of heart​" and not ichiban which'd be "#1" so idk what he means; also I changed the last time he called her that to intrepid too}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.16,0:02:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Cute little hamster!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.16,0:02:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you're also excited for the concert!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.51,0:02:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, bringing animals to the theater is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.58,0:02:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your problem? \NShe is quiet kid, alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.87,0:02:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn right!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.07,0:02:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,As a figure in this town, I swear by my name of Habersetzer \Nthat every member of my family is an epitome of propriety! {As a member of the prestigious House of Haberzetzer, you should be allowed to do this as proper; appropriate; due; suitable​}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.74,0:02:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My, some people are quick to fly off the handle! {unsure but likely "to get angry; to snap; to blow one's top; to lose one's temper; to flip"}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.37,0:02:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.51,0:02:39.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Munich's first prudish family. {lit is "elegant; refined; polished; stylish; sophisticated" but I think she means this in negative sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.48,0:02:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The girl next to Lotte is with them, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.72,0:02:47.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't take a good look...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.62,0:02:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what's the matter, Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.45,0:02:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe I went to sleep \Nwith an open window yesterday. {indisposition (e.g. a cold) caused by getting chilled while sleeping}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.20,0:02:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! Mom, they're starting!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.92,0:03:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, hide your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.69,0:03:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad's going to greet me now. {/will look here}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.08,0:03:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me I've caught a fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.11,0:04:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was as though I saw two Luises.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.48,0:04:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy seems to be slightly out of condition today.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.13,0:04:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't usually do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.92,0:05:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Something is definitely off. \N Is my mind playing tricks on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.89,0:05:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with him today?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.30,0:05:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He is not being his usual self.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.44,0:05:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,His music sounds unsteady. {not calm}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.77,0:05:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, we're in trouble if dad gets a good look at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.00,0:05:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.14,0:05:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.41,0:05:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You tell mom your head hurts, \Nthen escape to your right. {sounds a lot like nige he iku but gotta be migi}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.52,0:05:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, I'll escape to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.69,0:05:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.72,0:05:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We've no other choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.15,0:05:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, I'll have to go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.93,0:05:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.26,0:05:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a little headache.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.56,0:05:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch where you're going!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.76,0:05:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.03,0:05:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,AH! It hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.75,0:06:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a mouse!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.72,0:06:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Help, I can't stand them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.91,0:06:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.39,0:06:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough! Enough! Stop playing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.55,0:06:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The concert is disrupted!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.55,0:06:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, mom, I guess there's no point staying anyway. {/I'll go home first - repeating it here is pretty stupid}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.67,0:06:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, get some sleep when you're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.66,0:06:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Made it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.50,0:06:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought there was no saving us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.39,0:06:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,All thanks to Annie's hamster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.61,0:06:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Gonna thank her later!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.41,0:07:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, this all turned into such an uproar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.21,0:07:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure, dad is also mad now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.34,0:07:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My music is made into a hullabaloo! \NNot once in my life, I've been ridiculed like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.81,0:07:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right, everything that happened is our fault only.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.98,0:07:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of just one hamster, \Nthe entire concert is disrupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.35,0:07:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the first such debacle \Nin the history of our opera house, either. {most likely 当劇場始まって以来の大失態でございますから - it's It's the biggest blunder since the beginning of our theater}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.42,0:07:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough already!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.37,0:07:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try my patience and leave me alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.39,0:07:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.24,0:07:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.33,0:07:35.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.97,0:07:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Multiple local news magazines \Nare requesting a press conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.68,0:07:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Press conference?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.31,0:07:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do I have to explain it even to my manager?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.78,0:07:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not seeing a single soul more today!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.78,0:07:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My tuxedo! {. coat; jacket; outerwear}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.55,0:07:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Who had this bright idea of leaving it here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.65,0:07:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr... {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.42,0:07:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,did just five minutes ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.09,0:07:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! That I know myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.19,0:08:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, just arrange a car to the hotel now! {I hope h means this by pulling up; drawing up; salvage; re-flotation}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.63,0:08:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.03,0:08:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A dead end.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.80,0:08:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Press conference has been cancelled. Needless to say, \Nhe didn't give a single personal interview either. {to accept; to receive (an application); to take up}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.17,0:08:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, Palfy is retiring to hotel now. {again that pulling up; drawing up; salvage; re-flotation}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.29,0:08:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We've exhausted our options. {/we've no choice but to give up}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.19,0:08:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Exhausted? Don't say nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.45,0:08:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We've plenty of options to interview him \Nin the hotel! We need to hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.85,0:08:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I wash my hands of it. \NGoing that far is not something I'm prepared to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.83,0:08:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Be it for the Berlin concert last time, \Nbe it for today's one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.90,0:08:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,More than ever, the fans are eager \Nto hear some explanation from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.51,0:08:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting it out of him - \Nis the part and parcel of our work. {/telling it}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.52,0:08:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't imagine a worst time for an interview \Nthan that after such an uproar. {/he won't be in the mood for}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.94,0:08:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.22,0:08:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.35,0:09:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,For someone who usually stops at nothing, your willingness \Nto accept defeat in the matters pertaining Palfy is suspicious. {/... positive; assertive; active; proactive; aggressive, in palfy-related things, seem to be avoiding him}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.59,0:09:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a reason for that special treatment?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.90,0:09:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,None that I know of. \N No reason for special treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.64,0:09:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.87,0:09:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get you an interview from Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.24,0:09:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I wanted to hear!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.91,0:09:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,This article could only qualify as a professional one \Nif you, as someone educated in classical music, write it. {deep knowledge; attainments; scholarship}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.53,0:09:28.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a life-saver.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.45,0:09:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's not waste any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.49,0:09:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom is going...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.69,0:09:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,To meet dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.23,0:09:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.74,0:10:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Refusing an interview even now \Nis against the rules. {unsure maybe she means "it's been several hours since then"; also no clue what rules she refers to}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.48,0:10:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We have applied for it \Nthrough official channels three days ago. {/properly}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.19,0:10:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I try to talk him into it now, {/if you try to apply/talk to him}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.49,0:10:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy is still profoundly shocked \Nby the events of this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.29,0:10:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd probably say "I couldn't care less for interviews..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.69,0:10:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That would still be due to his personal issues - {I hope she means "that'll be a personal reason, it's unprofessional of the other party, we're doing business here"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.36,0:10:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,unacceptable in business.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.50,0:10:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Right... Well, I guess, I could ask him just once.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.14,0:10:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A lady journalist from Munich Graph.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.44,0:10:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She asserts that canceling an interview is against the rules, \Nand she just won't back off. {unsure, maybe he means "so you can't refuse" or "so she won't give up"}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.18,0:10:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hadn't she seen how my art got ruined barbarically?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.18,0:10:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not seeing anyone, \Nwhoever they call themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.05,0:10:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever they call themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.51,0:10:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Be it even Napoleon himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.23,0:10:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Be it even Cleopatra asking me out on a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.59,0:10:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Marilyn Monroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.98,0:10:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A flat "No!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.13,0:10:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, the journalists' ilk is the worst scum ever, \Ndoubly so for female journalists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.20,0:10:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? That in particular? How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.44,0:11:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, some years ago, \NI made a mistake of marrying an aspiring reporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.14,0:11:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even five minutes could pass \Nwithout us two quarreling. {/there was an average of one fight every 5 minutes}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.40,0:11:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, when first four minutes of marriage ran out, \Nmy happy family life was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.08,0:11:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,From the fifth minute on, \Nthe life had been but a chain of quarrels.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.31,0:11:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, at least for now, I've no idea where she is \Nor what she's up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.42,0:11:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But my point stands, the marriage is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.83,0:11:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What were we talking about, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.30,0:11:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,About a lady journalist, \Ndemanding an interview.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Just go there and tell them what I think. {rather, he says "go tell them to accept defeat" leaving; accepting but I'll add this to make a transition more smooth to the next scene}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.26,0:11:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What did you say? He had only been happy \Nfor the first four minutes of marriage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.84,0:11:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears, the nagging of his journalist wife \Ndid a number on him. {/his wife was an ill-tempered ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.04,0:11:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to blame him, \Nplease blame that woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.58,0:11:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.02,0:11:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell him that he is a selfish musician, \Nnot sticking to his promises.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.97,0:11:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,From here on, he doesn't deserve \Nso much as a footnote in our magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.13,0:11:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all just as she said. \NIf you excuse us...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.00,0:11:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.07,0:12:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all happening because we \Nturned the concert into a hullabaloo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.56,0:12:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Miss Körner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.64,0:12:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief, do you deem me a wonder-worker, \Ndemanding me to do anything more than that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.98,0:12:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you've done an excellent job.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.11,0:12:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, I was the one at fault, \Nasking you to do the impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.88,0:12:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, would you let me \Ntreat you to dinner as an apology?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.89,0:12:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I would gladly follow you elsewhere. {not sure what she means: I'll go out with you/keep you company}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.09,0:12:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If I stay here any longer, \NI would soon require something to vent my anger on. {cannot contain one's anger; can't contain myself; staying angry}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My, my. You can be pretty intimidating, did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.36,0:12:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If they go, mom would come home late again... {I'm not sure what she originally meant to say by "it seems, mom would be late"}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.97,0:12:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, let's return first \Nand use this time to formulate the future strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.74,0:12:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, take my word for it, \Nwhen I say your spirit of journalism was on its peak today. {/I admire your ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.54,0:12:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I should apologize \Nfor trying to abuse it. {unsure what he means: In that sense, I owe you an apology.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.31,0:12:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure need some nerve to say it like that. {/what a man}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.61,0:12:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you still mad with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.98,0:12:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What Palfy said back then is unforgivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.53,0:13:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you mean Palfy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.70,0:13:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, the men are all like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.32,0:13:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Blame his unhappiness on the marriage, \Nthus covering up his own shortcomings. {/he considers the marriage the start of his misfortunes, he decides so unilaterally, despite his own bad sides} {to fix upon (one-sidedly); to (ignore someone's position and) arbitrarily decide something is the case}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.98,0:13:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.65,0:13:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.68,0:13:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so do, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.15,0:13:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd never do something like that. {not sure if he means "I don't share your view" or "I'm not that kind of man"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.87,0:13:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.23,0:13:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad and mom only keep \Ndistancing each other further on. {to get complicated; to grow worse; to turn sour​}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.24,0:13:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.28,0:13:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine, if dad and mom remarry, \Nbut to their own new lovers... 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.68,0:13:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To their own new lovers?{/to different people}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.88,0:13:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Like whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.22,0:13:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if you think of it, mom could...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.32,0:13:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.72,0:14:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm convinced you live in a misconception. {misunderstanding; misapprehension; misconception; false impression; wrong idea}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.26,0:14:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I do? In a misconception?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.96,0:14:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The view the marriage is the source of unhappiness \Nis not necessarily shared by all men. {/the beginning of misfortunes}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.80,0:14:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Editor, have you ever \Nconsidered a marriage yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.83,0:14:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Most naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.17,0:14:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea. \NWho could she be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.15,0:14:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.48,0:14:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.92,0:14:34.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I must have taken a bit too much... {/overdrank}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.89,0:14:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, Miss Körner, \Nthat could be you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.66,0:14:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you ever think about entering a marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.60,0:14:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I must check on Lotte's headache...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.57,0:14:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Miss Körner?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.57,0:14:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, Editor, I'm worried about Lotte now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.50,0:15:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Most certainly! \NI didn't forget about Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.84,0:15:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, I think that little Lotte \Nshould be our mutual concern. {I hope he means this}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.39,0:15:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so caring, Editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.82,0:15:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing. \NI'm only doing what's natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.47,0:15:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I consider my part concluded here. {/will leave you hear}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.55,0:15:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My, won't you even come in to say hello to Lotte?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.64,0:15:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.83,0:15:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, only for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.95,0:15:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Lotte, we'll talk tomorrow again \Nto sort out the rest. {/we'll consult again}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.61,0:15:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. I'll be waiting for a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.66,0:15:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,See you, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.89,0:15:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.90,0:15:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, be my guest, Editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.12,0:15:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I really think there's no need \Nto walk you home any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.79,0:15:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.00,0:15:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She is back at a moment like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.79,0:16:00.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,Returning so soon? Lotte is probably still awake. \NShe'll be happy to see you. {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.40,0:16:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever, I'll hide in the bedroom for now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.77,0:16:03.07,Sign,,0,0,0,,I guess you're right. \NThen, I only show my face in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.07,0:16:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.75,0:16:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're back sooner than I thought, mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.62,0:16:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, is your headache gone already?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.75,0:16:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! Completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.35,0:16:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.39,0:16:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening, Herr Editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.21,0:16:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll make you some tea now. \NPlease wait in the living room.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.15,0:16:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.16,0:16:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, I'll distract them in the living room for now. {to detain; to check; to restrain; to stop}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.82,0:16:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Use that time to slip away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.94,0:16:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.57,0:16:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, I don't think I'll be staying for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.99,0:16:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.87,0:16:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,She has every right to feel exhausted. \NPlease make sure she gets a good rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.52,0:16:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now's my chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.55,0:16:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,See you, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.02,0:16:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.73,0:17:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,All is lost! \NWe're goners now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.45,0:17:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.54,0:17:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I must have overdrunk myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.73,0:17:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly see two Lottes instead of one!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.48,0:17:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's best that I get home soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.84,0:17:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't just stand here! {actually she says again "now's your chance"}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.92,0:17:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.42,0:17:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, Herr Editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.95,0:17:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Look...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.87,0:17:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Adorable Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.68,0:17:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, my little angel!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.81,0:17:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Drunk? {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.38,0:18:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,She sounds mighty lively. \NWhat's going on there? {lively (party, voices, etc.); loud; noisy; merry; cheerful}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.25,0:18:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom talks to herself sometimes. \NIt's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.36,0:18:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But say, Lotte, you mom sure is a caring person.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.95,0:18:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Her mind is with you at any given time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.77,0:18:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,She is Germany's number one caring mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.74,0:18:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But in being headstrong, \Nshe might just be number one in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.97,0:18:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just what I thought! {unsure, maybe he means "that's well said" or "that's a good thing about her"}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.34,0:18:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,She's nothing like the fragile women \Nthat you see everywhere around you. {she's different from delicately; weakly; gently; supplely​ woman who are common; run-of-the-mill; ordinary}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.28,0:18:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Her radiance of living by her own rules is unmistakable. {/she has her own way of life and it makes her shine}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.05,0:18:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Editor...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.42,0:18:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.19,0:18:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,To you and to your always beautiful mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.14,0:18:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.46,0:19:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It seems, she was too drunk \Nto tell me apart from the usual Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.75,0:19:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.66,0:19:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor Bernau is a caring and good man...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.49,0:19:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom! Don't you mean \Nyou consider marrying Herr Editor?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.10,0:19:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.02,0:19:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The commotion they caused at the concert, had once again \Nonly served to fan the flames of Lotte and Luise's worrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.43,0:19:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,With a new major problem \Narising before them all of a sudden, {to well up; to burst; to arise}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.60,0:20:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,will the two ever be able to overcome \Nboth it and their own doubts? {added}
Comment: 0,0:20:20.37,0:20:20.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.31,0:20:29.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.84,0:20:33.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.30,0:20:37.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.02,0:20:39.93,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.15,0:20:51.57,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.57,0:20:55.33,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.33,0:20:58.87,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.87,0:21:02.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.71,0:21:05.44,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.29,0:21:08.84,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.84,0:21:13.39,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.39,0:21:17.54,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.09,0:21:22.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.74,0:21:26.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.15,0:21:29.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.78,0:21:32.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.60,0:21:37.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.37,0:21:40.78,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:44.37,0:21:44.37,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.68,0:21:46.15,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.15,0:21:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, let's go for it. Make or break! {sink or swim; all or nothing; hit or miss; make or break}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.82,0:21:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll come up with a plan \Nto make dad and mom meet when they least expect! {unexpectedly (meeting someone)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.42,0:21:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try talking, at least...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.76,0:21:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Talking is not an option!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.16,0:22:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Somehow, we must make them get along again!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.45,0:22:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell what'll come out of this, \Nbut the plan certainly looks worth trying, Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.53,0:22:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be our last chance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.17,0:22:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.77,0:22:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.74,0:22:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad and Mom Meet Again.{お父さんとお母さんの再会}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.14,0:22:14.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 18\NDad and Mom Meet Again {お父さんとお母さんの再会}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.04,0:22:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Look forward to it!
